  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HDFC II Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project is in line with the Government of India&apos;s &quot;Housing for All by 2022&quot; initiative. The most significant, expected project-level outcome is increased access to financing for affordable housing for lower and middle-income segments. The Project will also support HDFC in gradually growing its nascent green housing portfolio. Beyond the Project, IFC anticipates that the investment, together with other IFC&apos;s efforts in the segment, will help promote greater competitiveness in affordable housing financing via demonstration and replication channels.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment comprises a senior debt investment of up to US$250 million in HDFC Limited (HDFC or the Company). The loan proceeds will be used to provide retail buyers financing for affordable housing with a mutually agreed portion of IFC funding to be earmarked for green affordable housing.</narrative>
  </description>
